  "description": "Semiosis is the process by which a [sign](./sign.md) produces an [interpretant](./interpretant.md), which, being itself a [sign](./sign.md), produces a further [interpretant](./interpretant.md), and so on. It is the dynamic, iterative process through which meaning is generated, propagated, and transformed.",
